y to intelligent design. We would do well to go beyond The Origin of Species and-taking as our guide such works as W. Wentworth Thomson's On Growth and Form acknowledging that evolutionary adaptation can result in solutions of a sort that intelligence could readily ratify. Accordingly, what the present book seeks is a naturalization of Intelligent Design that sees such design as itself the result of natural and evolutionary processes.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aEvolution (Biology)xPhilosophy. 0aIntelligent design (Teleology). 4aEvolutionstheorie. 4aIntellegent Design. 4aPhilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z9783110331219oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311031995840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110320145423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110320145.jpg  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DONb2012  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014